==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nawab
<hw>Na*wab"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Nabob</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A deputy ruler or viceroy in
India; also, a title given by courtesy to other persons of high rank in
the East.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rich, retired Anglo-Indian; a nabob.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nawl</ent>⟦br⟧
